verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 2Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, I am the Lord your God.

tokens.text: unto them, I am the Lord

verses.text_plain: After the doings of the land of Egypt, wherein ye dwelt, shall ye not do: and after the doings of the land of Canaan, whither I bring you, shall ye not do: neither shall ye walk in their ordinances.
verses.verse_html: 3After the doings of the land of Egypt, wherein ye dwelt, shall ye not do: and after the doings of the land of Canaan, whither I bring you, shall ye not do: neither shall ye walk in their ordinances.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall do my judgments, and keep mine ordinances, to walk therein: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 4Ye shall do my judgments, and keep mine ordinances, to walk therein: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall therefore keep my statutes, and my judgments: which if a man do, he shall live in them: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 5Ye shall therefore keep my statutes, and my judgments: which if a man do, he shall live in them: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: None of you shall approach to any that is near of kin to him, to uncover their nakedness: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
6None of you shall approach to any that is near of kin to him, to uncover their nakedness: I am the Lord. ▼
▼ near…: Heb. remainder of his flesh

footnotes.body_text: ▼ near…: Heb. remainder of his flesh
footnotes.body_html: ▼ near…: Heb. remainder of his flesh

verses.text_plain: The nakedness of thy father, or the nakedness of thy mother, shalt thou not uncover: she is thy mother; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 7The nakedness of thy father, or the nakedness of thy mother, shalt thou not uncover: she is thy mother; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.

verses.text_plain: The nakedness of thy father’s wife shalt thou not uncover: it is thy father’s nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 8The nakedness of thy father’s wife shalt thou not uncover: it is thy father’s nakedness.

verses.text_plain: The nakedness of thy sister, the daughter of thy father, or daughter of thy mother, whether she be born at home, or born abroad, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover.
verses.verse_html: 9The nakedness of thy sister, the daughter of thy father, or daughter of thy mother, whether she be born at home, or born abroad, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover.

verses.text_plain: The nakedness of thy son’s daughter, or of thy daughter’s daughter, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover: for theirs is thine own nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 10The nakedness of thy son’s daughter, or of thy daughter’s daughter, even their nakedness thou shalt not uncover: for theirs is thine own nakedness.

verses.text_plain: The nakedness of thy father’s wife’s daughter, begotten of thy father, she is thy sister, thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 11The nakedness of thy father’s wife’s daughter, begotten of thy father, she is thy sister, thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father’s sister: she is thy father’s near kinswoman.
verses.verse_html: 12Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father’s sister: she is thy father’s near kinswoman.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy mother’s sister: for she is thy mother’s near kinswoman.
verses.verse_html: 13Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy mother’s sister: for she is thy mother’s near kinswoman.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father’s brother, thou shalt not approach to his wife: she is thine aunt.
verses.verse_html: 14Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy father’s brother, thou shalt not approach to his wife: she is thine aunt.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy daughter in law: she is thy son’s wife; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 15Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy daughter in law: she is thy son’s wife; thou shalt not uncover her nakedness.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy brother’s wife: it is thy brother’s nakedness.
verses.verse_html: 16Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of thy brother’s wife: it is thy brother’s nakedness.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her daughter, neither shalt thou take her son’s daughter, or her daughter’s daughter, to uncover her nakedness; for they are her near kinswomen: it is wickedness.
verses.verse_html: 17Thou shalt not uncover the nakedness of a woman and her daughter, neither shalt thou take her son’s daughter, or her daughter’s daughter, to uncover her nakedness; for they are her near kinswomen: it is wickedness.

verses.text_plain: Neither shalt thou take a wife to her sister, to vex her, to uncover her nakedness, beside the other in her life time.
verses.verse_html:
18Neither shalt thou take a wife to her sister, to vex her, to uncover her nakedness, beside the other in her life time. ▼
▼ a wife…: or, one wife to another

tokens.text: beside the other in her life

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a wife…: or, one wife to another
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a wife…: or, one wife to another

verses.text_plain: Also thou shalt not approach unto a woman to uncover her nakedness, as long as she is put apart for her uncleanness.
verses.verse_html: 19Also thou shalt not approach unto a woman to uncover her nakedness, as long as she is put apart for her uncleanness.

tokens.text: as long as she is put apart

verses.text_plain: Moreover thou shalt not lie carnally with thy neighbour’s wife, to defile thyself with her.
verses.verse_html: 20Moreover thou shalt not lie carnally with thy neighbour’s wife, to defile thyself with her.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt not let any of thy seed pass through the fire to Molech, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
21And thou shalt not let any of thy seed pass through the fire to Molech, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the Lord. ▼
▼ Molech: Gr. Moloch

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not lie with mankind, as with womankind: it is abomination.
verses.verse_html: 22Thou shalt not lie with mankind, as with womankind: it is abomination.

verses.text_plain: Neither shalt thou lie with any beast to defile thyself therewith: neither shall any woman stand before a beast to lie down thereto: it is confusion.
verses.verse_html: 23Neither shalt thou lie with any beast to defile thyself therewith: neither shall any woman stand before a beast to lie down thereto: it is confusion.

tokens.text: thyself therewith: neither shall any woman

verses.text_plain: Defile not ye yourselves in any of these things: for in all these the nations are defiled which I cast out before you:
verses.verse_html: 24Defile not ye yourselves in any of these things: for in all these the nations are defiled which I cast out before you:

tokens.text: not ye yourselves in any of these things
for in all these the nations

verses.text_plain: And the land is defiled: therefore I do visit the iniquity thereof upon it, and the land itself vomiteth out her inhabitants.
verses.verse_html: 25And the land is defiled: therefore I do visit the iniquity thereof upon it, and the land itself vomiteth out her inhabitants.

tokens.text: thereof upon it, and the land

verses.text_plain: Ye shall therefore keep my statutes and my judgments, and shall not commit any of these abominations; neither any of your own nation, nor any stranger that sojourneth among you:
verses.verse_html: 26Ye shall therefore keep my statutes and my judgments, and shall not commit any of these abominations; neither any of your own nation, nor any stranger that sojourneth among you:

verses.text_plain: (For all these abominations have the men of the land done, which were before you, and the land is defiled;)
verses.verse_html: 27(For all these abominations have the men of the land done, which were before you, and the land is defiled;)

verses.text_plain: That the land spue not you out also, when ye defile it, as it spued out the nations that were before you.
verses.verse_html: 28That the land spue not you out also, when ye defile it, as it spued out the nations that were before you.

verses.text_plain: For whosoever shall commit any of these abominations, even the souls that commit them shall be cut off from among their people.
verses.verse_html: 29For whosoever shall commit any of these abominations, even the souls that commit them shall be cut off from among their people.

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall ye keep mine ordinance, that ye commit not any one of these abominable customs, which were committed before you, and that ye defile not yourselves therein: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 30Therefore shall ye keep mine ordinance, that ye commit not any one of these abominable customs, which were committed before you, and that ye defile not yourselves therein: I am the Lord your God.
